column5: Has anybody been there? If so, what's it like? any tips on where to go fishing? etc  Neil

I stayed there many times when it was the Lancaster House.  Great place and my buddy jsut got back from there two weekends ago.  They did ok, some OOS bass, perch, pike and walleye.  I am told there is a shoal with a weed bed right near the lodge.  Not 100% sure though.  It's a great place to spend the weekend.  Also, the old owner told us there were some monster walleye under the boat dock so give that a go. Sherriff
